  <steps>
    <step num="0">Heat the olive oil in a large pan over high heat, then add the jalapeños, onion, garlic, and salt. Stir and cook for 4 minutes. </step>
    <step num="1">Add the water and vinegar. Reduce the heat to medium-low. </step>
    <step num="2">Simmer for 20 minutes stirring continuously. </step>
    <step num="3">Remove the pan from the heat and let cool. </step>
    <step num="4">Pour the jalapeño mixture into a blender and puree until smooth. </step>
    <step num="5">Using a funnel, pour the sauce into a bottle or jar and store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
